close_reason: "Feature goals met: status alias normalization implemented, regressions covered, and docs updated."
body: "Feature plan: add centralized status normalization utility, wire all status entry points, and preserve canonical in_progress persistence for backwards compatibility.\n\n## Detailed implementation plan\n1. Add a shared status normalization helper in core item utilities that:\n   - Accepts canonical statuses and alias spellings (`in-progress` -> `in_progress`).\n   - Normalizes case/whitespace and returns canonical enum values.\n   - Preserves deterministic validation errors for unsupported statuses.\n2. Wire the helper into every status input boundary:\n   - `pm create --status`\n   - `pm update --status`\n   - `pm calendar --status`\n   - `pm test-all --status`\n   - importer status adapters (`beads`, `todos`)\n   - item-document front-matter parsing/normalization for compatibility reads.\n3. Keep persisted status canonical:\n   - Storage and output remain `in_progress`.\n   - Alias support is input-compatible only to avoid schema churn.\n4. Extend regression coverage:\n   - Unit tests for create/update/calendar/test-all status alias behavior.\n   - Integration coverage validating CLI usage with `in-progress` and canonical readback.\n5. Update documentation and release notes:\n   - README, PRD, AGENTS usage notes, CHANGELOG `[Unreleased]`.\n6. Verify end-to-end safety:\n   - Build, targeted unit/integration runs, and full sandbox-safe regression run.\n   - Record evidence on tasks/features/epic before closure."
